hu.invitech.insight.processor.sdk.v1.api

Interface RemoteInterface


  • public interface RemoteInterface
    Provides a service for handling processor lifecycle and receiving data from resources.

    This service is accessible at the baseUrl provided in the server's token (see ServerInterface.assignServer(ServerInfo))

    Version:
    1

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Sends received incoming data from a resource to the server.

      Tells the server that this processor has stopped.

    • Method Detail

      • start

        void start(Status status)
        Tells the server that this processor has started, and starts a data sync if needed.

        Needs JWT bearer authorization and returns HTTP 401 if the token is missing or invalid.

        Accessible at the following path: POST /v1

        HTTP status codes
        Code Text Description
        403 Forbidden The token is not assigned or it is assigned to a different processor than the caller
        204 No Content OK
        Parameters:
        status - the current status of this processor in relation to the server on which this method is called (see Status)
        Since:
        version 1

      • sendData

        void sendData(IncomingData data)
        Sends received incoming data from a resource to the server.

        Needs JWT bearer authorization and returns HTTP 401 if the token is missing or invalid.

        Accessible at the following path: POST /data/v1

        HTTP status codes
        Code Text Description
        403 Forbidden The token is not assigned or it is assigned to a different processor than the caller
        400 Bad Request An incoming data type with the name in IncomingData.type doesn't exist
        404 Not Found A resource with the id in IncomingData.resourceId doesn't exist
        204 No Content OK
        Parameters:
        data - the data received from a resource (see IncomingData)
        Since:
        version 1

      • stop

        void stop()
        Tells the server that this processor has stopped.

        Needs JWT bearer authorization and returns HTTP 401 if the token is missing or invalid.

        Accessible at the following path: DELETE /v1

        HTTP status codes
        Code Text Description
        403 Forbidden The token is not assigned or it is assigned to a different processor than the caller
        204 No Content OK
        ForbiddenException if the token is not assigned or it is assigned to a different processor than the caller
        Since:
        version 1
